<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-faqs">FAQs</h2>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-how-do-you-score-stableford-points-i=
n-golf">How do you score Stableford points in golf?</h3>



<p>To score more, you need to make more eagles, birdies, and pars. These eq=
ual the highest number of points to help you score the most. Unless it=E2=
=80=99s a modified Stableford scoring, where bogeys and worse are penalized=
, the goal should be to play aggressively. Especially on every par 5 and if=
 there is a drivable par 4! &nbsp;</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_8_tablet"=
 class=3D"adthrive-ad adthrive-sticky-container adthrive-content adthrive-c=
ontent-8 adthrive-ad-cls"></div>



<p>You want to give yourself as many opportunities as possible to make bird=
ies as you can score the most from them. But a par is a good score too. And=
 you never know, maybe an eagle putt will fall in as well for a huge win! &=
nbsp;</p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-how-do-i-score-points-in-golf">How d=
o I score points in golf?&nbsp;</h3>



<p>Normally, golf rewards the player who shoots the lowest score, not the =
=E2=80=9Cmost points.=E2=80=9D But this scoring system is the exact opposit=
e and the player who scores the highest number wins.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The way to score the most points in this system is to have the most eagl=
es, birdies, and pars while having fewer bogeys, doubles, or worse. Essenti=
ally, not much changes in terms of golf, you just want to make par and bird=
ies but maybe take a few more risks, so you can get a higher total score.</=
p>



